What is Sonic Cleansing?
Sonic cleansing means that the head/bristles of the brush oscillate at a sonic frequency (127Hz). The rapid movement of the brush’s bristles gently deep cleanses the skin, by removing residues, clearing pores and lightly exfoliating the skin.

Sonic facial cleansing brushes are not a staple, but if you are looking for a deeper cleanse, or looking to pamper your skin, you can definitely go for one. The Luna 3 by @foreo_in is hands down the best out there. It has a cleanser in the front and a massager at the back, and it is a silicone brush, which means it is perfect for sensitive skin, and also safe from bacterial build up. 

Thank you Team Foreo for sending it!

latestIgtvVideos.title: COVID-19 and hair fall💈
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
💁‍♀️ Anything we do to our hair, whether stressful or nourishing, will show changes only after 3-6 months! 

💁‍♀️ Telogen effluvium is a form of reversible hair fall that occurs after a stressful event. That event can be an illness (covid or otherwise), emotional stress, major life changes such as pregnancy, chemical treatments to hair or crash diets!

💁‍♀️ Telogen effluvium shows up 3-6 months after your stressful event and can stay upto 6-9 months after the stress factor has been removed

💁‍♀️Upto 100 hair falling a day is normal. In Telogen effluvium you may lose upto 3 times that!

💁‍♀️If you feel like your hairfall is more than usual, first always take lifestyle changes to see if there is an improvement

💁‍♀️ Remember that no shampoo or conditioner will treat hairfall!

💁‍♀️ However, if you are undergoing severe hairfall, or it is accompanied by pain, itching, bald patches or has come on very suddenly - please visit a dermatologist!

Have you experienced this? Let me know in the comments!

latestIgtvVideos.title: The BEST of @ilanaorganics - honest review
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#AD
I had seen @ilanaorganics at a tiny stall at @thelilflea almost 3years ago or more! Back then there weren’t many options for Indian #vegan skincare and makeup. The international ones were wayyyy out of budget for me! Also I had my friend’s bday coming up (she is vegan!)
Enter ilana! Ended up buying a lot of their products as a gift to her and she loved them :)

And here I am reviewing ilana! I’m truly surprised how life comes full circle 😅

💧I’ve been using their makeup cleansing balm as part of my double cleanse routine and also as a single cleanser when I feel like I need a bit of a hydration!

🍉 their watermelon essence is a product I’ve mentioned earlier as well - in my post on ‘post inflammatory erythema’ its got licorice which we know is one of the safest ingredients for #pigmentation in pregnant and breastfeeding women! It also contains centella, HA and AHAs 

🍓and finally their superstar product - the beet cheek and lip tint! I was so pleasantly surprised by the colour payoff! Just 2 drops and I was sorted throughout the day! Also loved their watery consistency! I thought I would mess it up cos I’m not very good with makeup but it went on really well! Also cos it was watery I didn’t have to worry about it getting cakey or pore clogging!

Let me know how you like these elaborate reviews! And what other brands/products you’d like to see reviewed here!

Ilana organics is available online and also on @sublimelifeofficial - you can get a 10% discount on using code DRMANASI

Here’s why ⬇️

⚠️ Sunscreen is toxic
✅ Sunscreen is classified as SAFE by the USFDA and many international regulatary bodies. It is proven to protect skin from UV damage & skin cancer.

⚠️ ‘Clean’ beauty = better
✅ “Clean” isn’t a regulated term, science-backed ingredients matter more.

⚠️ Acne is caused by dirty skin
✅ Acne has many causative factors; you could have great hygiene and still get acne.

⚠️ 10 step skincare routine is superior
✅ A simple, consistent routine beats overwhelming steps.

⚠️ Glass skin for Indian skin
✅ Glass skin is a trend, not a realistic goal for all skin types.

⚠️ Drinking 8 glasses of water a day = clear skin
✅ Hydration doesn’t guarantee clear skin

⚠️ More actives give glowing skin
✅ Too many actives irritate skin; moderation is 🗝️

⚠️ The harder you scrub, the better the result
✅ Harsh scrubbing damages skin, gentle and tender exfoliation works best.
